	('gjSEEQAAQBAJ', 'Fourteen Days To Love', NULL, 'Somnath Bhattacharjee', 'Somnath Bhattacharjee', '2025-09-04', 'Fourteen Days in Paris. A love to remember. When Sam, a Scottish history and language nerd, leans in to help a stranger struggling at a Paris hotel desk, he doesn’t expect to change the course of his life. Ana, the mysterious Russian girl he rescues with his words, shares his love for history, stories, and soon they grow something deeper, a bond, some untold feelings, an untold love. As they express their feeling, it\'s already the end of the holiday, he must return to Edinburgh, she to Moscow. Can love survive across borders, languages, and distance? Or be another lost love and fade as a lost memory.', NULL, NULL, 135, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=gjSEEQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=gjSEEQAAQBAJ&pg=PT127&dq=psychological+thriller+2023+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=4&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:42:51'),
	('gKN5EQAAQBAJ', 'Frankenstein', NULL, 'Mary Shelley', 'Chartwell', '2025-02-11', 'In the age of AI, this classic tale of technology gone wrong is a must-read collectible in this handsome faux-leather hardcover edition. The combination of fantastical elements and scientific exploration makes this Mary Shelley novel one of the first true models of science fiction. Frankenstein; or, The Modern Prometheus pioneered the deeply explored battle between monster and man. Follow three narratives in this ageless tale that navigates fear, fixation, love, and desire, while finding an anchor in humanity. The story comes alive anew in this beautifully designed edition featuring: An elegant faux-leather cover with foil-embossed designs An introduction by writer and English professor Catherine Steindler An author\'s introduction A timeline of the life and times of Mary Shelley This gorgeous, heirloom-quality collection is an ideal edition for classic book lovers to acquire for their home library. Essential volumes for the shelves of every classic literature lover, these deluxe classics editions include beautifully presented works from some of the most important authors in literary history. Other Chartwell Deluxe Editions include Little Women, Alice\'s Adventures in Wonderland, The Essential Tales and Poems of Edgar Allan Poe, The Essential Grimm\'s Fairy Tales, Anne of Green Gables, The Inferno, Dracula, The Republic, The Iliad, Meditations, and Irish Fairy and Folk Tales.', '0785846247', '9780785846246', 247, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=gKN5EQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=gKN5EQAAQBAJ&pg=PA203&dq=science+fiction+novel+2025+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=15&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:43:14'),
	('gmvQEAAAQBAJ', 'MR. BIG WEALTHS Unraveling the Secrets: A Guide to Crafting an Engaging Mystery/Psychological Thriller Book 2023', NULL, 'MR. BIG WEALTH', 'MR. BIG WEALTH', '2023-08-11', 'Introducing "MR. BIG WEALTHS | Unraveling the Secrets: A Guide to Crafting an Engaging Mystery/Psychological Thriller Book | 2023." This meticulously crafted guide takes aspiring authors on an immersive journey into the world of mystery and psychological thrillers, unlocking the secrets to crafting captivating narratives that will keep readers on the edge of their seats. Whether you are a seasoned writer or a novice looking to dive into the genre, this guide provides a wealth of knowledge, techniques, and insider tips to help you create a gripping masterpiece. With MR. BIG WEALTHS as your guide, you will learn how to intricately weave suspense, develop complex characters, build atmospheric settings, and deliver unexpected twists that will leave readers yearning for more. Immerse yourself in the art of storytelling and bring your own mystery or psychological thriller to life with "Unraveling the Secrets." Get ready to captivate and thrill readers with a book that will have them eagerly turning the pages until the very end.', NULL, NULL, 86, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=gmvQEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=gmvQEAAAQBAJ&pg=PA12-IA2&dq=thriller+novel+2023+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=3&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:42:48'),
	('gNQ9EQAAQBAJ', '2024 Top Ten Gay Romance', NULL, 'J.M. Snyder, Alexandra Caluen, Holly Day, Nell Iris, Shawn Lane, K.L. Noone, Mere Rain, Ellie Thomas, Alexander Verlangen, Alex Winters, Patrick Bryce Wright', 'JMS Books LLC', '2024-12-28', '2024 Top Ten Gay Romance brings together the best-selling short stories published by JMS Books that year. From first love to true love, from submission to sensual, from heat to sweet and everything in between, the couples in these stories are sure to keep you turning the pages as you fall in love with them. With stories by Alexandra Caluen, Holly Day, Nell Iris, Shawn Lane, K.L. Noone, Mere Rain, Ellie Thomas, Alexander Verlangen, Alex Winters, and Patrick Bryce Wright, this head-over-heels collection goes beyond bedtime reading. Whether happily ever after or happy for now, there\'s an ending for everyone in here! Contains the stories: Empty Shelves, Full Hearts by Alexandra Caluen The Snaccident by Holly Day Snowstorm Confessions by Nell Iris Glad Tidings by Shawn Lane Midwinter Music by K.L. Noone Three Wishes and a Miracle by Mere Rain The Way Home by Ellie Thomas Roses, Romps, and Romance by Alexander Verlangen The Do Over by Alex Winters A New Season of Intimacy by Patrick Bryce Wright', '1685508693', '9781685508692', 529, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=gNQ9EQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=gNQ9EQAAQBAJ&pg=PT518&dq=YA+thriller+2024+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=8&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:42:11'),
	('Gp6BEQAAQBAJ', 'A Room with a View', NULL, 'E.M. Forster', 'Broadview Press', '2025-08-27', 'This updated edition of E.M. Forster’s 1908 classic renders A Room with a View newly accessible to contemporary readers. What may appear to be a straightforward romance, lighter and brighter than the novels Forster would go on to write, has darker undertones as well. The protagonist, Lucy Honeychurch, struggles with the constraints of gender and class expectations, and may seem to triumph over them—but A Room with a View deliberately resists the easy satisfactions of a happy ending. Instead, Forster leaves us with the uneasy sense that there is more to the story, and it is our job to discover it in the nuanced twists and turns of his narrative. Meticulously detailed footnotes and thoughtfully chosen appendices bring the early-twentieth-century Florence of the novel to life. Contemporary reviews of the book, along with relevant essays and other non-fiction writings by Forster and his contemporary, Virginia Woolf, add helpful literary and historical context.', '1037700376', '9781037700378', 320, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Gp6BEQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=Gp6BEQAAQBAJ&pg=PA310&dq=contemporary+fiction+2025+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=17&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:43:42'),
