	('NhhzEAAAQBAJ', 'Harlequin Romantic Suspense May 2023 - Box Set', NULL, 'Beth Cornelison, Karen Whiddon, Tara Taylor Quinn, Amber Leigh Williams', 'Harlequin', '2023-04-25', 'Looking for heart-racing romance and breathless suspense? Want stories filled with life-and-death situations that cause sparks to fly between adventurous, strong women and brave, powerful men? Harlequin® Romantic Suspense brings you all that and more with four new full-length titles in one collection! COLTON\'S UNDERCOVER SEDUCTION (A The Coltons of New York novel) by Beth Cornelison To investigate the Westmore family, rookie cop Eva Colton goes undercover as ladies\' man detective Carmine DiRico\'s wife on a marriage-retreat cruise. As the "marriage" starts feeling alarmingly real, Eva becomes the lone witness to a shipboard murder and the target of a killer determined to silence her…permanently. SAVED BY THE TEXAS COWBOY by Karen Whiddon When Marissa Noll\'s former high school sweetheart and now-injured rodeo star Jared Miller returns to Anniversary, Texas, and needs her help with physical therapy, she vows to be professional. After all, she\'s moved on with her life. But when she starts receiving threats, the coincidental timing makes her wonder if Jared might have something to do with it. THE BOUNTY HUNTER\'S BABY SEARCH (A Sierra\'s Web novel) by USA TODAY bestselling author Tara Taylor Quinn Haley Carmichael discovers her recently deceased sister had a baby—a baby who\'s currently missing— and she knows her ex-husband, Paul Wright, is the only one who can help. Reuniting with his ex is the last thing the expert bounty hunter wants, but he isn\'t willing to risk a child\'s life, either—and a second chance might help both of them put past demons to rest. HUNTED ON THE BAY by Amber Leigh Williams Desiree Gardet will change her address, her name, her hair—anything—to leave her past behind, but when fate brings her to sweet and sexy barkeep William Leighton and the small town he calls home, she longs for somewhere to belong more than ever before. Unfortunately, her past has a way of catching up with her no matter what she does, only this time Desiree finds that she isn\'t alone in the crosshairs.', '0369728424', '9780369728425', 996, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=NhhzEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=NhhzEAAAQBAJ&pg=PT981&dq=romantic+suspense+2023+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=1&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:42:44'),
	('NJieEAAAQBAJ', 'Dead Again (Defenders of Battle Mountain, Book 6) (Mills & Boon Heroes)', NULL, 'Nichole Severn', 'HarperCollins UK', '2023-05-11', 'Can he trust her again?', '0008932239', '9780008932237', 195, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=NJieEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=NJieEAAAQBAJ&pg=PT1&dq=romantic+suspense+2023+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=7&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:42:44'),
	('NLXiEAAAQBAJ', 'Los viajes de Gulliver', 'Clásicos de la literatura', 'Jonathan Swift', 'DigiCat', '2023-12-03', 'Los viajes de Gulliver es una obra maestra de la sátira política y social escrita por Jonathan Swift en 1726. A través de los viajes del protagonista, Lemuel Gulliver, el libro explora diversas sociedades fantásticas, cada una de ellas representando una crítica mordaz a la realidad contemporánea de la Inglaterra del siglo XVIII. Swift emplea un estilo irónico y un lenguaje claro y preciso que permite una reflexión profunda sobre la naturaleza humana, la política, y la moralidad. Su contexto literario se inscribe en la tradición de la literatura de viajes y la sátira, posicionándose como un precursor del relato fantástico moderno, al tiempo que explora la complejidad de la condición humana a través de la alegoría y el sarcasmo. Jonathan Swift, escritor y satirista irlandés, fue un crítico agudo de la sociedad de su tiempo. Su experiencia como clérigo anglicano y su desilusión con la política británica lo impulsaron a utilizar la literatura como una plataforma para expresar su descontento. Influenciado por el contexto sociopolítico de la época y las injusticias que observaba a su alrededor, Swift diseñó Los viajes de Gulliver como un medio para cuestionar la razón y el sentido de la civilización, llevándonos a ver lo absurdo a través de los ojos de Gulliver en tierras lejanas. Recomiendo encarecidamente Los viajes de Gulliver a cualquier lector que busque una obra rica en significado y crítica social. Este libro no solo brinda entretenimiento a través de sus travesías fantásticas, sino que también invita a la reflexión sobre los valores de la modernidad y la hipocresía que muchas veces se oculta tras las normas sociales. Es un texto esencial que perdura en el tiempo y que sigue resonando en las discusiones sobre la ética y la política.', NULL, NULL, 315, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=NLXiEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'es', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=NLXiEAAAQBAJ&pg=PT6&dq=ciencia+ficci%C3%B3n+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=19&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:36:52'),
	('nOoX0ViUlPgC', 'Red Harvest', NULL, 'Dashiell Hammett', 'Vintage Crime/Black Lizard', '2010-12-29', 'From one of the great pioneers of detective stories, a classic novel reissued with a new introduction by S.A. Cosby The steadfast and sturdy Continental Op has been summoned to the town of Personville—known as Poisonville—a dusty mining community splintered by competing factions of gangsters and petty criminals. The Op has been hired by Donald Willsson, publisher of the local newspaper, who gave little indication about the reason for the visit. No sooner does the Op arrive, than the body count begins to climb . . . starting with his client. With this last honest citizen of Poisonville murdered, the Op decides to stay on and force a reckoning—even if that means taking on an entire town. Red Harvest is more than a superb crime novel: it is a classic exploration of corruption and violence in the American grain.', '0307767485', '9780307767486', 225, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=nOoX0ViUlPgC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=nOoX0ViUlPgC&pg=PR7&dq=detective+novel+2023+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=19&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:43:01'),
	('NqD3EAAAQBAJ', 'Modern Romance August 2024 Books 1-4: Greek Pregnancy Clause (A Diamond in the Rough) / Her Impossible Boss\'s Baby / Fast-Track Fiancé / Billion-Dollar Dating Game', NULL, 'Maya Blake, Millie Adams, Amanda Cinelli, Natalie Anderson', 'HarperCollins UK', '2024-08-01', 'Four red hot romances from Mills & Boon! Greek Pregnancy Clause Maya Blake Her freedom... for a price!', '0008940010', '9780008940010', 718, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=NqD3EAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=NqD3EAAAQBAJ&pg=PT1&dq=contemporary+romance+2024+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=1&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:42:39'),
	('NQs9EQAAQBAJ', 'Crafting for Sinners', 'A Novel', 'Jenny Kiefer', 'Quirk Books', '2025-10-07', '“You will compulsively turn these pages well into the dead of night.”—Paul Tremblay, New York Times best-selling author of Horror Movie and The Cabin at the End of the World A queer woman must fight her way out of a craft store run by a megachurch in this gripping survival horror novel by Jenny Kiefer, author of This Wretched Valley. The ratcheting tension and gut-churning terror will appeal to fans of Camp Damascus by Chuck Tingle and Horrorstör by Grady Hendrix. Ruth is trapped. She’s stuck in her small, religious hometown of Kill Devil, Kentucky, stuck in the closet, and stuck living paycheck to paycheck. After her manager finds out that she lives with her girlfriend, Ruth is fired from her job at New Creations—a craft store owned by the church that dominates life in Kill Devil. In an act of revenge, Ruth attempts to shoplift some yarn but is caught red-handed. Instead of calling the police, the employees lock her in the store—and attack her. As Ruth fights for her life using only the crafting supplies at hand, she plunges deeper into the tangled web of the New Creationists, who are hiding a terrible secret that threatens not only her but the entire town. Urgent, scathing, and utterly original, Crafting for Sinners cements Kiefer’s status as a dazzling new star in horror.', '1683694716', '9781683694717', 32, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=NQs9EQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=NQs9EQAAQBAJ&pg=PA2&dq=horror+novel+2024+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=1&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:43:06'),
	('nqsnEQAAQBAJ', 'Understanding (Post)feminist Girlhood Through Young Adult Fantasy Literature', NULL, 'Elizabeth Little', 'Taylor & Francis', '2024-11-04', 'Understanding (Post)feminist Girlhood Through Young Adult Fantasy Literature takes advantage of growing critical interest in popular young adult texts and their influence on young people. The monograph offers an innovative approach by pairing traditional literary analysis with the responses of readers to show the complex ways that young people respond to the depiction of female protagonists. In the first section, the book utilises a feminist framework to examine young adult fantasy novels published from 2012 to 2018, with a particular focus on A Court of Thorns and Roses (Maas, 2015) and Red Queen (Aveyard, 2015). The analysis shows how strong female protagonists in young adult fantasy are postfeminist heroines who reinscribe patriarchal power structures, embrace limited understandings of gender roles, and persist in relationships that oppress them. In the second section, the monograph introduces empirical data from a series of focus groups discussing those same novels. The discussion shows that readers respond to these popular young adult fantasy texts with complexity and nuance that highlights their postfeminist subjectivities as they simultaneously reject and reinscribe elements of postfeminism in their understanding of the girl protagonists.', '1040216749', '9781040216743', 183, 'Young Adult Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=nqsnEQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=nqsnEQAAQBAJ&pg=PA160&dq=young+adult+fantasy+2024+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=1&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:42:06'),
	('Nr7NEAAAQBAJ', 'Three France Crime Thrillers In One Volume July 2023', NULL, 'Alfred Bekker', 'Alfredbooks', '2023-07-27', 'This volume includes the following thrillers: Marquanteur And The Foundation Marquanteur And The Strangler Of Marseille Marquanteur And The Revenge Clément Degresse is actually in the old factory building to close an illegal deal. But he quickly realizes that it is a trap. Someone wants to make him pay for a crime he was involved in years ago. Commissaire Marquanteur of the Marseille Criminal Investigation Department must stop an ice-cold vendetta, but every detail of this bloody revenge seems well planned. Alfred Bekker is a well-known author of fantasy novels, thrillers and books for young people. In addition to his major book successes, he has written numerous novels for suspense series such as Ren Dhark, Jerry Cotton, Cotton Reloaded, Kommissar X, John Sinclair, and Jessica Bannister. He has also published under the names Neal Chadwick, Jack Raymond, Jonas Herlin, Dave Branford, Chris Heller, Henry Rohmer, Conny Walden, and Janet Farell.', '3745232305', '9783745232301', 362, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=Nr7NEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=Nr7NEAAAQBAJ&pg=PT8&dq=crime+thriller+2023+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=1&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:42:54'),
	('NrCNEQAAQBAJ', 'Stone - The Adventures of Rhone & Stone', NULL, 'Strider S.R. Klusman', 'Duramen Publishing', '2021-11-23', 'You know you\'re lonely when your best friend is a rock. Stone - A genre-crossing, action-adventure, alien contact, survival story. Orphaned at thirteen, Rhone lives a solitary life on the old homestead, doing what needs doing but not much more. But his life changes when he finds a pretty rock in the shallow river near his home and sticks it in his pocket. Then he starts hearing things. Stone, the stone-like crystalline entity is eons old with tons of data stored in its crystalline matrix, but even with that knowledge it takes time to learn the difference between knowing by thinking, and knowing by doing. Two different things entirely. When the local commissioner sends his men to find, buy, or steal what he considers is an artifact of power, Rhone, and his new friend Stone, head to the badlands, a place named for a very good reason, but a chance encounter by The Commissioner\'s men ends up with Stone being taken, and Rhone left for dead. Luckily, the OPR is aware of the commissioner\'s heavy-handed ways and unknowingly helps Rhone to free Stone and find their way to freedom. An unforgettable story of unique friends, trust, and learning, set in an Old West setting. Stone, book one of,The Adventures of Rhone Stone. From award-winning author, Strider S.R. Klusman. For those who enjoyed the blend of sci-fi and western in "The Gunslinger" by Stephen King, you\'ll enjoy Stone, by Strider S.R. Klusman.', NULL, '9798985119633', 457, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=NrCNEQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=NrCNEQAAQBAJ&pg=PT453&dq=young+adult+fiction+2024+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=11&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:42:06'),
	('NUHmEAAAQBAJ', 'Detective Hamilton Cleek: 8 Thriller Classics in One Premium Edition', 'Cleek of Scotland Yard, Cleek the Master Detective, Cleek\'s Government Cases, Riddle of the Night', 'Thomas W. Hanshew, Mary E. Hanshew', 'Good Press', '2023-12-06', 'Detective Hamilton Cleek: 8 Thriller Classics in One Premium Edition offers readers a thrilling dive into the Edwardian detective genre, presenting a mosaic of narratives teeming with suspense, mystery, and psychological intrigue. Encompassing a diverse range of literary styles from the era, the anthology encapsulates the evolution of detective storytelling, marked by intricate plots and a compelling protagonist. Each story stands out for its unique approach, enriching the collection with a tapestry of suspenseful tales that maintain Cleek\'s enigmatic brilliance and unparalleled deductive skills at their core. The stories, drawn from the creative minds of Thomas W. Hanshew and Mary E. Hanshew, collectively portray the vibrant ingenuity of the early 20th-century detective fiction landscape. These authors are at the intersection of the Golden Age mysteries and Edwardian literary trends, bringing together elements of crime, adventure, and science. Their collaborative narratives delve into social nuances and human psychology, thus reflecting the complexities of their time and adding depth to the detective genre\'Äôs traditional formula. This anthology is a treasure trove for avid readers and scholars alike, offering a compelling gateway into the world of early detective fiction. The collection not only entertains but also educates, presenting varied literary voices that contribute to a holistic understanding of the genre\'s evolution. Readers are invited to engage with a multiplicity of thrilling perspectives, making it an invaluable addition to any literary collection or personal library.', NULL, NULL, 2061, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=NUHmEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=NUHmEAAAQBAJ&pg=PT3&dq=crime+thriller+2023+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=13&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:42:54'),
