	('zOpjEQAAQBAJ', 'The Grim Ripper (A Ripple Effect Mystery, Book 8)', NULL, 'Jeanne Glidewell', 'ePublishing Works!', '2023-05-02', 'The Tables Are Turned When Sleuthing Seniors, Rip and Rapella, Investigate a Doc\'s Mysterious Death in The Grim Ripper, A Cozy Mystery Adventure from Jeanne Glidewell When Rip experiences chest pain, Dr. Marco Moretti brings a new lease on life. But when the good doctor drops dead in the parking lot, Rip\'s wife, Rapella, dives head-first into investigating the doctor\'s mysterious demise. When the doctor\'s death is ruled "by natural causes," the Ripples are skeptical. But later, when it changes to "homicide," Rapella quickly compiles a list of suspects, including another heart surgeon and several nurses. Now with Rip on the mend from his arterial stent surgery, the retired full-time RVers take on the case together, proving that retirement can be a risky lifestyle. Publisher\'s Note: The Ripple Effect series will be enjoyed by fans of Joanne Fluke, Madison Johns, Ceecee James, and readers of cozy mysteries who enjoy light-hearted, clean & wholesome, mysteries featuring female amateur sleuths and senior citizens. REVIEWS "Glidewell succeeds in maintaining a rapidly paced storyline that dramatically builds suspense, while her tongue-in-cheek sense of humor provides plenty of laugh-out-loud moments." — Booklist on Leave No Stone Unturned "Jeanne Glidewell\'s mysteries are fast-paced, complex, and has just the right hint of romance." — Jill Churchill, author of the Jane Jeffry and Grace and Favor Mysteries "Being Rip and Rapella\'s age, I am happy to see them featured in adventures." — Anna, Reviewer THE RIPPLE EFFECT MYSTERIES A Rip Roaring Good Time Rip Tide Ripped to Shreds Rip Your Heart Out Ripped Apart No Big Rip The Grim Ripper Rip Chord THE LEXIE STARR MYSTERIES Leave No Stone Unturned The Extinguished Guest Haunted With This Ring Just Ducky The Spirit of the Season Cozy Camping Marriage and Mayhem Jeanne Glidewell lives with her husband, Bob, a Vietnam veteran, in the small coastal town of Rockport, Texas, where they enjoy life along Salt Lake, just off Copano Bay. When she isn\'t writing, Jeanne loves wildlife photography, fishing, and traveling—whether exploring the Irish countryside, hiking volcanic trails in the Galapagos Islands, or photographing wildlife closer to home. As a kidney and pancreas transplant recipient, Jeanne is a passionate advocate for organ and tissue donation, encouraging others to consider the life-saving gift of becoming a donor. Jeanne is the author of the Lexie Starr cozy mystery series, a New York Times best-seller that includes seven novels and a holiday novella, the Ripple Effect cozy mystery series, and a romance-suspense novel, Soul Survivor. Her mysteries combine humor, small-town charm, and page-turning suspense. You can learn more about her books at www.jeanneglidewell.com.', '1644573210', '9781644573211', 296, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=zOpjEQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=zOpjEQAAQBAJ&pg=PT283&dq=mystery+novel+2024+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=9&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:42:56'),
