	('zv3bEAAAQBAJ', 'Prince\'s Forgotten Diamond (Diamonds of the Rich and Famous, Book 2) (Mills & Boon Modern)', NULL, 'Emmy Grayson', 'HarperCollins UK', '2024-05-09', 'He’s forgotten everything...but their forbidden desire!', '0008935688', '9780008935689', 201, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=zv3bEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=zv3bEAAAQBAJ&pg=PT26&dq=romance+novel+2024+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=16&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:42:20'),
	('zx3xEAAAQBAJ', 'The Best American Short Stories 2024', NULL, 'Lauren Groff, Heidi Pitlor', 'HarperCollins', '2024-10-22', 'A collection of the year’s best short stories, selected by celebrated bestselling author Lauren Groff, author of Matrix and The Vaster Wilds, and series editor Heidi Pitlor. “There have never been as many exquisitely built stories in existence than there are now,” proclaims guest editor Lauren Groff in her introduction. This abundance led to a volume of robust stories with the nerve to push against narrative expectations. The Best American Short Stories 2024 boasts a collection of twenty stories that “buzz with their own strange logic.” A man becomes a tourist in his own hometown. An unemployed jeweler sails in an antique slave ship. A therapist decides to call an ex-patient years after their last session. Daring and resonant, the stories in this volume invite in Groff “a feeling that both the author and I were simultaneously discovering something together.” The Best American Short Stories 2024 includes JAMEL BRINKLEY • ALEXANDRA CHANG • LAURIE COLWIN • MOLLY DEKTAR • TAISIA KITAISKAIA • DANIEL MASON • JIM SHEPARD • AZAREEN VAN DER VLIET OLOOMI • PAUL YOON • and others', '006327597X', '9780063275973', 293, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=zx3xEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=zx3xEAAAQBAJ&pg=PT10&dq=gothic+horror+2024+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=2&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:43:06'),
	('ZxnzEAAAQBAJ', 'Campus Killer (The Lynleys of Law Enforcement, Book 5) (Mills & Boon Heroes)', NULL, 'R. Barri Flowers', 'HarperCollins UK', '2024-07-04', 'An undeniable attraction...', '0008939624', '9780008939625', 211, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ZxnzEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=ZxnzEAAAQBAJ&pg=PT1&dq=romantic+suspense+2024+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=20&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:42:42'),
	('zXPzEAAAQBAJ', 'Living Hell (An Urban Romantasy Romance Novel)', NULL, 'Celia Kyle', 'Celia Kyle', '2024-04-04', 'The dead aren’t rising in Mouse Town anymore, but banishing them cost a lot. More than expensive shoes. More than a sports car. We’re talking the kind of price that only comes from gnarly magic: Sam’s memories of me. He has no idea who I am. Can I even be his mate anymore? Hell if I know, and I don’t have time to deal with it all. Because there’s a twisted sorcerer in town. Before I can focus on my love life, I need to stop him from stripping magical DNA from anyone who catches his fancy so he can make my cousin his bride. Not a chance. But there’s something going on inside of me, something that makes me feel too small in my skin, as if the trials I endured to stop the last bad guy have awakened some power deep within. With Sam out of the picture and my bestie keeping her distance—for some reason—I have to deal with this on my own. That’s the way it always goes. Sam and I have overcome so many supernatural hardships, but this time I don’t know if there’s a way to get him back.', NULL, NULL, 232, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=zXPzEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=zXPzEAAAQBAJ&pg=PT231&dq=romantasy+2024+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=2&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:42:14'),
	('zXs2EQAAQBAJ', 'The Case-Book of Sherlock Holmes', NULL, 'Sir Arthur Conan Doyle', 'First Avenue Editions TM', '2025-01-01', 'First published in 1927, Arthur Conan Doyle\'s final twelve Sherlock Holmes stories follow the detective Holmes and his companion, Dr. John Watson, through unique and thrilling mysteries. The crime-solving duo discover the truth behind many bizarre cases, including a soldier\'s strange illness and a woman\'s dangerous affair with a circus performer. This collection of short stories concludes Doyle\'s tales of the beloved detective.', NULL, '9798765652053', 237, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=zXs2EQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=zXs2EQAAQBAJ&pg=PT3&dq=detective+novel+2024+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=10&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:42:56'),
	('ZYPvEAAAQBAJ', 'Bajo tierra seca', 'Premio Nadal de Novela 2024', 'César Pérez Gellida', 'Ediciones Destino', '2024-02-07', 'PREMIO NADAL 2024 6.a edición Extremadura, principios del siglo xx. Antonia Monterroso, más conocida como la Viuda, es la propietaria de una de las mayores haciendas de la región; intenta mantenerla a flote en un momento en el que la hambruna que afecta las zonas rurales no parece terminar jamás. Pero un incendio destruye todo lo que con tanto empeño ha logrado construir y, tras él, ella desaparece sin dejar rastro. El teniente Martín Gallardo se desplaza hasta el lugar junto con el sargento Pacheco para investigar lo sucedido. Cinco días atrás, la mujer interpuso una denuncia contra Jacinto Padilla, capataz de su finca y antiguo amante, a quien han detenido en la estación de Zafra con una bolsa llena de dinero y joyas. Él asegura que provocó el incendio por orden de Antonia y que la bolsa se la entregó ella porque iban a empezar una nueva vida lejos de allí. Durante el interrogatorio, Padilla confiesa una serie de hechos macabros que provocan un giro radical en una investigación que acabará tiñéndose de sangre. Gallardo, como todos los que viven por la zona, ha oído hablar de la enigmática Viuda, pero lo que todavía no sabe es que se enfrenta a un caso del que no saldrá indemne. Bajo tierra seca es un thriller rural al más puro estilo Gellida sobre una mujer que marcó el destino de quienes se cruzaron con ella.', '8423365085', '9788423365081', 417, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ZYPvEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'es', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=ZYPvEAAAQBAJ&pg=PT4&dq=YA+thriller+2024+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=15&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:43:38'),
	('_hESEQAAQBAJ', 'A Day at the Beach', NULL, 'Gary D. Schmidt, Ron Koertge', 'HarperCollins', '2025-04-01', 'Look Both Ways meets Seedfolks in this masterful novel from two titans of kid lit that follows a diverse cast of young people whose lives intersect in surprising and hilarious ways over the course of a summer day. Here’s what’s so cool about the beach. Kids are everywhere! Kids you know, kids you want to know. Wandering from one blanket to another, from one family to another. Somebody’s mom reads a fat summer novel. Somebody’s dad snores with an iPad on his chest. Babies cry. Girls laugh. Frisbee players whoop! Kites in the perfect blue sky. Some kids bodysurf. Some don’t even like the water. They build sand cities for their friends and sand jails for the grown-ups, and when the tide comes in everything gets washed away. There’s the other world, where all kids hear is tomorrow, next week, next year. And then there’s the beach, where everything is right now! Why can’t every day be a day at the beach? From two-time Newbery honoree Gary D. Schmidt and two-time PEN Award winner Ron Koertge comes a moving and often laugh-out-loud funny middle grade novel about family, friendship, and belonging, told by a group of kids spending a day at the beach. Thoughtful vignettes brilliantly weave together an irresistible tale of tween conflict and connections.', '0063380943', '9780063380943', 156, 'Juvenile Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=_hESEQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=_hESEQAAQBAJ&pg=PT152&dq=young+adult+fiction+2025+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=6&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:43:30'),
	('_MOYEAAAQBAJ', 'Boy Parts', 'A Novel', 'Eliza Clark', 'HarperCollins', '2023-05-23', 'One of Granta\'s Best Young British Novelists 2023 An incendiary debut novel from a brash new talent—a pitch-black comedy, both shocking and hilarious, which fearlessly explores sexuality and gender roles in the twenty-first century. “Hallucinogenic, electric and sharp, Boy Parts is a whirlwind exploration of gender, class, and power.”—Jessica Andrews, author of Saltwater Exiled from the art world and on sabbatical from her dead-end bar job, Irina obsessively takes explicit photographs of the average-looking men she persuades to model for her, scouted from the streets of Newcastle. But her talent has not gone unnoticed, and Irina is invited to display her work at a fashionable London gallery. It is a chance to revive her career and escape from the rut of drugs, alcohol, and extreme cinema she’s fallen into. Yet the news instead triggers a self-destructive tailspin, centered around Irina’s consuming relationship with her best friend, and a shy young man from her local supermarket who has attracted her attention. . . .', '0063328933', '9780063328938', 271, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=_MOYEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=_MOYEAAAQBAJ&pg=PP1&dq=horror+novel+2023+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=13&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:43:07'),
	('_O-cEAAAQBAJ', 'Sins And Seduction: The Ruthless Rival: Enemies with Benefits (The Mortimers: Wealthy & Wicked) / The Prince\'s Stolen Virgin / One Night with His Rival', NULL, 'Zara Cox, Maisey Yates, Robyn Grady', 'HarperCollins UK', '2023-01-05', 'Awakened by desire', '0008930961', '9780008930967', 527, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=_O-cEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=_O-cEAAAQBAJ&pg=PT1&dq=YA+fantasy+2023+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=17&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:42:08'),
	('_Q0HEQAAQBAJ', 'Love Inspired Suspense March 2025 - Box Set 2 of 2', NULL, 'Terri Reed, Kellie VanHorn, Susan Gee Heino', 'Harlequin', '2025-02-25', 'Love Inspired Suspense brings you three new titles! Enjoy these suspenseful romances of danger and faith. This box set includes: TRAINED TO PROTECT by Terri Reed K-9 officer Tarren McGregor never imagined that a cartel would find its way to Texas’s South Padre Island—or target his best friend’s sister. But when Julia Hamilton witnesses and prevents the kidnapping of a teen girl, Tarren knows that trouble is soon to follow. Because Julia didn’t just protect the girl—she saw the abductor’s face. Now she’s marked for murder, and it’s up to Tarren and his K-9 partner to keep Julia safe from the human traffickers in pursuit…even if it means putting themselves in the line of fire. WYOMING RANCH SABOTAGE by Kellie VanHorn Desperate to rescue her horses from a suspicious fire, rancher Sadie Madsen suddenly finds herself trapped inside the burning barn instead. She’s saved by the one man she never wanted to see again—her ex-fiancé, Jesse Taylor. Unable to ignore the string of recent “accidents” on her property, Sadie reluctantly accepts the park ranger’s help. But as they investigate and discover family secrets, the attacks escalate. Dangerous killers want Sadie’s land, and luring the culprits into the open is their only hope of escaping a deadly conspiracy… A DANGEROUS PAST by Susan Gee Heino When police officer and chaplain Gabe Elliot hears a disturbing deathbed confession, he turns to the one person who can help—the fiancée he left behind ten years ago. As the small town’s archivist, Brinna Jenson has the skills to investigate the fifty-year-old murder. And she’s determined to find out whether her best friend’s dying grandfather is responsible for covering up a heinous crime. But between break-ins and threats, a shadowy figure pursues them. If Brinna and Gabe want to claim their second chance at love, they’ll have to survive… For more stories filled with danger and romance, look for Love Inspired Suspense March 2025 Box Set – 1 of 2', '0369756452', '9780369756459', 589, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=_Q0HEQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=_Q0HEQAAQBAJ&pg=PT56&dq=thriller+novel+2025+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=2&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:42:45'),
	('_R_jEAAAQBAJ', 'CHRISTMAS MYSTERIES - 20 Thriller Classics in One Volume', 'Murder Mysteries & Intriguing Stories of Suspense, Horror and Thrill for the Holidays', 'Charles Dickens, Robert Louis Stevenson, Arthur Conan Doyle, Thomas Hardy, John Kendrick Bangs, Nathaniel Hawthorne, Grant Allen, Wilkie Collins, O. Henry, Saki, William Douglas O\'Connor, Catherine Crowe, Louisa M. Alcott, M.R. James, G.K. Chesterton, Leonard Kip, Emmuska Orczy', 'DigiCat', '2023-12-11', 'CHRISTMAS MYSTERIES – 20 Thriller Classics in One Volume offers a captivating tapestry of suspense, intrigue, and festive curiosities. This anthology brings together a versatile array of narratives that merge the magic of the holiday season with the chilling allure of mystery. From tales of spectral visitations to cunning detective exploits, the collection spans an impressive range of literary styles and settings. The unpredictable twists and atmospheric storytelling of these works highlight the complexity and riches of Gothic and Victorian traditions, delivering a punchy and evocative sense of the era\'s innovations. Each story, whether set in a fog-laden street or a glimmering winter wonderland, beckons the reader to unravel its secrets. The ensemble of authors in CHRISTMAS MYSTERIES includes luminaries such as Charles Dickens, Arthur Conan Doyle, and Louisa M. Alcott, each contributing to the literary vibrancy of the nineteenth and early twentieth centuries. These writers, shaped by distinct historical and cultural movements, offer a cornucopia of insights into human nature, society, and morality. As part of the broader tapestry of Gothic and detective literature, their works illuminate the interplay between light and shadow, joy and fear, that define the Christmas experience, enriching it with layers of psychological and social commentary. This collection not only serves as a testament to the enduring appeal of suspenseful storytelling but also an invitation to experience the breadth and depth of literary craft across storied traditions. Readers are encouraged to immerse themselves in these tales for their educational value and the immersive experience of various narrative voices. CHRISTMAS MYSTERIES stands as a celebration of diverse perspectives, seamlessly inviting dialogue between authors and readers, and offering a delightful foray into the art of thrilling literature during the most enchanting time of the year.', NULL, NULL, 610, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=_R_jEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=_R_jEAAAQBAJ&pg=PT11&dq=YA+thriller+2023+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=8&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:43:07'),
	('_sbiEAAAQBAJ', 'A. J. Raffles, A Gentleman-Thief: 27 Crime Tales in One Volume', 'The Amateur Cracksman, The Black Mask - Raffles: Further Adventures, A Thief in the Night & Mr. Justice Raffles', 'E. W. Hornung', 'DigiCat', '2023-12-09', 'In "A. J. Raffles, A Gentleman-Thief: 27 Crime Tales in One Volume," E. W. Hornung presents a series of interconnected stories that uniquely blend crime fiction with elements of adventure and intrigue. Through the captivating exploits of A. J. Raffles, a debonair burglar with a penchant for high society, Hornung employs a narrative style rich in wit and sophistication, echoing the sentiments of late Victorian literature. Raffles embodies the charming yet elusive antihero, providing a counterpoint to the traditional detective tales of the era, particularly those of his brother-in-law, Arthur Conan Doyle\'s Sherlock Holmes, thus establishing a novel perspective within the genre by celebrating the thief rather than the pursuer. E. W. Hornung, an accomplished writer and playwright, was deeply influenced by his personal experiences, having spent time in London\'s elite circles. His close relationship with Conan Doyle, along with his exposure to the criminal underbelly of society during this period, shaped his fascination with Raffles\' character. This duality of admiration and rebellion reflects Hornung\'s exploration of morality through the lens of theft, ultimately positioning Raffles as a romantic figure amid his nefarious deeds. I highly recommend "A. J. Raffles, A Gentleman-Thief" to aficionados of classic crime fiction and readers seeking a rich tapestry woven with charm, cleverness, and social commentary. This collection not only entertains but also invites readers to question the nature of crime and nobility, making it an essential addition to the libraries of both new and seasoned enthusiasts of the genre.', NULL, NULL, 617, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=_sbiEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=_sbiEAAAQBAJ&pg=PR1&dq=crime+thriller+2023+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=16&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:42:54'),
	('_ZlYEQAAQBAJ', 'Eli and Jay\'s Love Story, Eventually', NULL, 'Eve Morton', 'JMS Books LLC', '2025-03-29', 'Eli and Jay have known one another since they were children. Their life on the Star Belt government reserve in Saskatchewan isn\'t great, but the people -- like Tantoo, Eli\'s grandmother, Jay\'s sisters, and grandmother Buffy -- have always made life tolerable. Until the day Jay kissed Eli only to be rejected, and a moment of misunderstanding drives the two friends apart for years, a misunderstanding that won\'t come up again until tragedy draws them together once more.', '1685509762', '9781685509767', 115, 'Fiction', 'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=_ZlYEQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api', 'en', 'http://books.google.es/books?id=_ZlYEQAAQBAJ&pg=PT104&dq=romantic+fiction+2023+after:2000&hl=&as_brr=6&as_pt=BOOKS&cd=16&source=gbs_api', '2026-02-13 16:42:24');
